cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.AI 

This paper discusses the impact of policy interventions on the Internet to counter malware, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The use of an agent-based model to investigate the impact of policy interventions suggests the possibility of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) being used in the research. The paper also discusses the effectiveness of coordinated efforts, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY), and the comparison of different countermeasures, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
